The prevalence of asthma or chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) in
psoriasis patients in the random effects model is of 2.7% (CI 95%: 1.3-5.5;
Figure 4).

The prevalence of ischemic cardiomyopathy or coronary insufficiency in
psoriasis patients in the random effects model is of 3.4% (CI 95%: 2.3-5%;
Figure 11).

Other prevalent comorbidities in psoriasis patients were alexithymia; other
dermatological conditions such as seborrheic dermatitis, acne, rosacea;
pulmonary hypertension; and celiac disease (Table 1).
